title: Bug 4121 - JarExporter causes out of Sync (1GILQD5)
description: The JarExporter is causing out of sync issues.
OB: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported jar in the same directory (project), an out of sync message is displayed when overwriting the exported jar file for the second time.
EB: The JarExporter should allow overwriting the exported jar file without displaying an out of sync message.
SR:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the project
2. Export the directory
3. Place the exported jar in the same directory
4. Overwrite the exported jar file
5. Check for any out of sync messages
